  {
    "chapterId": "s-block-elements",
    "correctOptionIndex": -1,
    "exam": "jee-advanced",
    "marks": 3,
    "negativeMarks": 1,
    "question": {
      "en": {
        "content": "<p><b>Statement-1 :</b> Alkali metals dissolves in liquid ammonia to give blue solutions</p>\n<p><b>Statement-2 :</b> Alkali metals in liquid ammonia give solvated species of the type $$\\left[\\mathrm{M}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_{3}\\right)_{n}\\right]^{+} (\\mathrm{M}=$$ alkali metals).</p>",
        "correct_options": [
          "B"
        ],
        "explanation": "<h3><strong>Statement-1 :</strong></h3>\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Alkali metals dissolve in liquid ammonia to give blue solutions.  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>✅ <strong>True</strong></p>\n<p>Explanation: When alkali metals (Li, Na, K, etc.) are dissolved in liquid ammonia, they form deep blue conducting solutions at low concentrations.  </p>\n<p>Reaction:</p>\n<p>$ \\mathrm{M (s) \\xrightarrow{liq.\\,NH_3} M^+_{(solv)} + e^-_{(solv)}} $</p>\n<p>The blue color arises from <strong>solvated electrons</strong> ($ e^-_{(NH_3)} $), which absorb visible light.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Statement-2 :</strong></h3>\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Alkali metals in liquid ammonia give solvated species of the type $\\left[\\mathrm{M}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_{3}\\right)_n\\right]^+ (\\mathrm{M} = \\text{alkali metals})$.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>✅ <strong>True</strong></p>\n<p>During dissolution, the metal forms <strong>metal cations solvated by ammonia molecules</strong>, i.e., $\\mathrm{M^+}$ surrounded by several $\\mathrm{NH_3}$ molecules.</p>\n<p>$ \\mathrm{M^+ + e^- \\rightarrow [M(NH_3)_n]^+ + e^-_{(solv)}} $</p>\n\n<h3>But:</h3>\n<p>The <strong>blue color</strong> (Statement-1) is <strong>not</strong> due to $[\\mathrm{M(NH_3)_n}]^+$, but due to the <strong>solvated electrons</strong> ($e^-_{(NH_3)}$).  </p>\n<p>Therefore, although both statements are true, <strong>Statement-2 does not explain the blue color</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>✅ <strong>Final Answer :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Option B</strong> — Statement-1 is True, Statement-2 is True; Statement-2 is <strong>NOT</strong> a correct explanation for Statement-1.</p>",
        "options": [
          {
            "content": "Statement-1 is True, Statement-2 is True; Statement-2 is a correct explanation for Statement-1",
            "identifier": "A"
          },
          {
            "content": "Statement-1 is True, Statement-2 is True; Statement-2 is NOT a correct explanation for Statement-1",
            "identifier": "B"
          },
          {
            "content": "Statement-1 is True, Statement-2 is False",
            "identifier": "C"
          },
          {
            "content": "Statement-1 is False, Statement-2 is True",
            "identifier": "D"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
