    "chapterId": "s-block-elements",
    "correctOptionIndex": -1,
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "exam": "jee-advanced",
    "marks": 1,
    "negativeMarks": 0.25,
    "question": {
      "en": {
        "content": "The substance absorbs CO<sub>2</sub> and violently reacts with water. The substance is",
        "correct_options": [
          "B"
        ],
        "explanation": "<p>The correct answer to the question is Option B: CaO.</p>\n\n<p>Let's break down the reasoning:</p>\n\n<p><strong>CaO</strong> (Calcium oxide), also known as quicklime, vigorously reacts with water to form calcium hydroxide (Ca(OH)<sub>2</sub>) and releases a significant amount of heat. This reaction is known as slaking of lime and can be represented as:</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\text{CaO} + \\text{H}_2\\text{O} \\rightarrow \\text{Ca(OH)}_2 $$</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, calcium oxide has a strong affinity for carbon dioxide (CO<sub>2</sub>). It absorbs CO<sub>2</sub> from the air to form calcium carbonate (CaCO<sub>3</sub>) through the following reaction:</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\text{CaO} + \\text{CO}_2 \\rightarrow \\text{CaCO}_3 $$</p>\n\n<p>Thus, CaO fulfills both conditions: it absorbs CO<sub>2</sub> and reacts violently with water. The other substances listed do not meet these criteria:</p>\n\n<p><strong>CaCO<sub>3</sub>:</strong> Calcium carbonate reacts with acids but does not react violently with water and does not absorb CO<sub>2</sub>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>:</strong> Sulfuric acid is a liquid that reacts vigorously with water (specifically, dilution of concentrated sulfuric acid is exothermic), but it does not absorb CO<sub>2</sub>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>ZnO:</strong> Zinc oxide is an amphoteric oxide that does not react violently with water and does not absorb CO<sub>2</sub>.</p>\n\n<p>Therefore, the most appropriate answer is:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option B</strong>: CaO</p>",
        "options": [
          {
            "content": "CaCO<sub>3</sub>",
            "identifier": "A"
          },
          {
            "content": "CaO",
            "identifier": "B"
          },
          {
            "content": "H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>",
            "identifier": "C"
          },
          {
            "content": "ZnO",
            "identifier": "D"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    "question_id": "xleMsw9qQBAisR7J",
    "solution": "",
    "subject": "chemistry",
    "title": "IIT-JEE 1978",
    "topic": "physiochemical-trends-in-alkaline-earth-metals",
    "type": "MCQ",
    "year": 1978
